# Course Builder Project Rules

## Python Environment
- The Python virtual environment is at the PROJECT ROOT: `/home/ubuntu/github/jmjava/course-builder/.venv`
- Always use `.venv/bin/python` and `.venv/bin/pip` from the project root
- To run tests: `cd /home/ubuntu/github/jmjava/course-builder && .venv/bin/pytest`
- To install packages: `.venv/bin/pip install <package>`

## Project Structure
- `phase1/` - QGIS-based satellite imagery acquisition and boundary extraction
- `phase2a/` - SAM-based mask generation and interactive feature selection
- `course-builder/` - Java Spring Boot backend with React frontend

## Testing Commands
- Run phase2a tests: `.venv/bin/pytest phase2a/tests/ -v`
- Run specific test file: `.venv/bin/pytest phase2a/tests/test_svg.py -v`
- Skip GUI tests: `.venv/bin/pytest phase2a/tests/ -v --ignore=phase2a/tests/test_gui_integration.py`

## SVG Output Format
- Generated SVGs should match the Inkscape-compatible format in `phase2a/resources/RockRidge_No_Overlay.svg`
- Use inline styles with `opacity:0.5;fill:#XXXXXX` instead of CSS classes
- Use `inkscape:label` on paths for feature type identification
- Layer groups use `inkscape:groupmode="layer"` and `inkscape:label="HoleN"`
